						               													<description>End fast, but the grudge will last long!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Kongkang is a party card game based on a traditional card game from Southern Thailand called &amp;quot;Kang&amp;quot;. Players try to get rid of high cards and match those previously played to steal Banana tokens. When someone declares &amp;quot;Kongkang&amp;quot;, everyone reveals their hand, and the player who has the lowest hand wins the pot. After three rounds, the player with the most banana tokens wins!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;At the beginning of the first round, deal 5 cards to each player. Everyone places 2 Banana tokens in the center of the table as a pot for the round. On your turn, you must perform one of the following actions:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Draw a card and play any number of identical cards. If they are special cards, resolve the action for each card.&amp;#10;     Follow the card(s) played by the previous player. First, play any number of cards that match the followed card(s). Then, steal that many Banana tokens from that player. However, if that player also followed the previous player, instead steal from the player who first played the card(s).&amp;#10;     Declare Kongkang. Everyone reveals all cards in their hand and compute their total value (with special card being worth 10). The player with the lowest total wins the round and claims all Banana tokens from the pot, where a tie goes to the one closest to (and including) the declarer in turn order. In addition, if the declarer didn't win, they discard half the Banana tokens to the game box.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;When a player draws the last card from the deck, the next player is forced to declare Kongkang. After the winner is determined, a new round begins with these changes.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     The winner of the round becomes the first player for the next round. &amp;#10;     Players with the most Banana tokens place 4 tokens in the pot, and those with the fewest Banana tokens place 1 token. Everyone else places 2 tokens as usual.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
